e economic and social interactions and crystallizing social relations among villagers local elites and markets based on ethnographic research on the autumn harvest in a township in northern china this study sheds light on distinctive modes of market transactions across produces and diverse interactions between markets and local institutions involving different co ordination mechanisms rhythms and social relationships a more nuanced image of market transactions emerges from these observations calling for a more refined conceptualization of markets and further research on their implications for institutional changes download html+ go to site external http journals cambridge org abstr topics business china search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages publications of interest the road to collective debt in rural china bureaucracies social institutions and public goods provision xueguang zhou modern china 2011 html+ cover rural land and labor markets in the process of economic development evidence from china scott rozelle klaus deininger songqing jin zude xian 2005 pdf+ the collective foundation of rapid rural industrialization jean c oi eduard b vermeer frank n pieke woei lien chong me sharpe in cooperative and collective in china's rural development between state and private interest 1997 buy+ markets and income inequality in rural china political advantage in an expanding economy andrew g walder american sociological review vol 67 no 2 2002 pdf+ cover support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
